WEBVTT

00:04.371 --> 00:06.106 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening. I'm
Judy Woodruff.

00:06.206 --> 00:12.279 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:
Floating wreckage
proves EgyptAir Flight 804
crashed in the

00:12.379 --> 00:19.019 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mediterranean, but there remain
more questions
than answers as to what brought
down the plane.

00:19.119 --> 00:25.025 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also ahead: Food labels are
about to get a
makeover. The first lady and the
FDA overhaul

00:25.125 --> 00:30.430 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
rules to include added sugar and
other changes
to promote healthier eating.

00:30.530 --> 00:37.137 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Then: The candidates talk
foreign policy,
as worries rise about party
unity. Mark Shields

00:37.237 --> 00:41.475 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and David Brooks take on that
and more of
the week's news.

00:41.575 --> 00:47.214 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And ahead of President Obama's
trip to Vietnam,
a look at how the U.S.
ambassador to the country

00:47.314 --> 00:51.852 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is doing away with traditional
modes of diplomacy
and jumping into the culture.

00:51.952 --> 00:58.458 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
