Vietnam: The
fact that I show respect for
Vietnamese language

00:58.558 --> 01:02.930 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and culture and history, the
Vietnamese people,
the fact that I show that
respect, that I

01:03.030 --> 01:07.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
clearly enjoy being here, I
think that has
helped my mission.

01:07.100 --> 01:15.008 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:15.108 --> 01:17.878 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:17.978 --> 01:28.889 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: They have found
some of what's
left of EgyptAir Flight 804, and
new clues

01:28.989 --> 01:33.927 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
may be emerging in the
investigation. The
passenger plane vanished from
the radar early

01:34.027 --> 01:39.232 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
yesterday, en route from Paris
to Cairo, with
66 people on board.

01:39.333 --> 01:41.335 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
John Yang reports on the day's
developments.

01:41.435 --> 01:49.409 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: At a Cairo mosque,
families of
passengers aboard EgyptAir
Flight 804 prayed,

01:49.509 --> 01:51.278 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and wept, for loved ones.

01:51.378 --> 01:55.048 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ABDEL RAHMAN AL NASERY, Cousin
of Passenger
(through translator): He was my
cousin. He

01:55.148 --> 01:59.619 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was like an elder brother to me.
This is very
hard for the family, and God
bless all who

01:59.720 --> 02:01.555 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
died on the plane.

02:01.655 --> 02:07.027 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Their hopes dashed by
the discovery
of wreckage from the Airbus
A-320 announced

02:07.127 --> 02:08.996 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
on Egyptian state television.

02:09.096 --> 02:15.302 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN (through translator): We
have just received
an official report from the
Egyptian army.

02:15.402 --> 02:19.272 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Military airplanes have been
able to locate
wreckage and belongings of the
airplane.

02:19.373 --> 02:23.110 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: The Greek defense
minister recounted
the grisly details.

02:23.210 --> 02:27.748 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PANOS KAMMENOS, Greek Defense
Minister (through
translator): We have been
briefed about the

02:27.848 --> 02:32.953 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
discovery of a body part, two
seats and luggage
at the scene of the search,
slightly to the

02:33.053 --> 02:35.088 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
south of where the plane's
signal was lost.

02:35.188 --> 02:39.860 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: A European satellite
image showed
an oil slick spreading over the
area where

02:39.960 --> 02:45.599 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the plane disappeared. Debris
was spotted
floating in the Mediterranean
about 180 miles

02:45.699 --> 02:52.472 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
north of Alexandria, Egypt. It's
an area were
the sea is up to two miles'
deep, but still

02:52.572 --> 02:55.776 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
no firm evidence of what
happened.

02:55.876 --> 03:02.749 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Late today, what could be a
significant clue:
The Aviation Herald, an online
aviation community,

03:02.849 --> 03:07.888 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
reported that an automated
monitoring system
on the plane sent signals
indicating smoke

03:07.988 --> 03:14.895 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in the front of the cabin and
then failures
of two key control systems
before going silent.

03:14.995 --> 03:21.568 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Egyptian officials had initially
suggested
a terror attack as the likeliest
explanation,

03:21.668 --> 03:26.239 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but the Greek defense minister
said today
it's just too early to tell.

03:26.339 --> 03:31.311 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
PANOS KAMMENOS (through
translator): There
is no possibility to assess the
situation.

03:31.411 --> 03:35.315 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We cannot be part of the
speculation, because
the investigation committee must
be allowed

03:35.415 --> 03:37.250 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to do its work.

03:37.350 --> 03:41.888 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: The French navy is
helping scour
the sea, and its investigators
said no possible

03:41.988 --> 03:44.191 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
causes are being ruled out.

03:44.291 --> 03:48.595 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEAN-MARC AYRAULT, French
Minister of Foreign
Affairs (through translator):
All hypotheses

03:48.695 --> 03:53.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are being examined. There is no
specific one
being favored. We have to find
the debris

03:53.300 --> 03:58.238 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and analyze it, and of course
the black boxes,
because we want to know the
truth, the whole

03:58.338 --> 04:00.173 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
truth.

04:00.273 --> 04:04.811 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: So far, there's no
hard evidence
of an explosion. But from Cairo
to Paris and

04:04.911 --> 04:07.547 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
beyond, speculation centers on
terrorism.

04:07.647 --> 04:14.087 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVEN SIMON, Dartmouth College:
They can't
pretend that it wasn't or
completely suspend

04:14.187 --> 04:15.889 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
judgment. They have to check the
locks.

04:15.989 --> 04:20.327 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Steven Simon served
on President
Obama's National Security
Council. He says

04:20.427 --> 04:23.430 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
officials have to investigate it
as a possible
terror attacks.

04:23.530 --> 04:28.268 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVEN SIMON: They will look to
see if any
of the identities of any of the
people on

04:28.368 --> 04:36.076 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the airplane, the crew, the
maintenance team,
anybody who had anything to do
with that airplane

04:36.176 --> 04:43.016 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
while it was on the ground in
Paris, they
will just go through, you know,
those records

04:43.116 --> 04:49.156 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with a fine-tooth comb, looking
for dots to
connect, if indeed there are
any.

04:49.256 --> 04:54.261 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: At the same time, he
says, Europe
has to work on beefing up
counterterrorism

04:54.361 --> 04:56.229 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
efforts.

04:56.329 --> 05:00.667 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVEN SIMON: It's sort of a
cumulative process.
You can't throw a lot of money
at something

05:00.767 --> 05:08.808 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and expect radical changes in
six months.
This is going to be a
transformative process

05:08.909 --> 05:12.012 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the European context which
will take a
while to complete.

05:12.112 --> 05:19.085 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: As the search for
what, or perhaps
who, brought down Flight 804
presses ahead.

05:19.186 --> 05:21.855 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm John
Yang.

05:21.955 --> 05:27.260 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So far, there's
been no claim
by any outside group that it had
a hand in

05:27.360 --> 05:29.196 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
bringing down the plane.

05:29.296 --> 05:33.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Here to talk through some of the
many questions
still out there is our science
correspondent

05:33.500 --> 05:36.303 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and aviation analyst, Miles
O'Brien.

05:36.403 --> 05:43.143 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Miles, first, this automated
data that became
known this afternoon, what do
you make of

05:43.243 --> 05:44.644 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
that?

05:44.744 --> 05:46.846 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Well, just a
quick bit of background
for our viewers.

05:46.947 --> 05:53.186 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is -- as an aircraft flies
around, it's
essentially live-streaming its
condition,

05:53.286 --> 05:57.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
its health of various systems.
It's mostly
for maintenance, so when the
plane lands,

05:57.190 --> 06:01.127 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
they know what parts to have
ready and what
to fix it to get it back in the
air again.

06:01.228 --> 06:06.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There were a series of faults
apparently right
before the plane disappeared
from radar, beginning

06:06.766 --> 06:12.072 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with some problems with the
windshield in
the cockpit, smoke in the
lavatory and in

06:12.172 --> 06:17.444 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the avionics bay, which is
beneath the cockpit,
and then some failures of the
computer systems.

06:17.544 --> 06:21.348 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are literally hundreds of
computer systems
controlling this aircraft. They
all have to

06:21.448 --> 06:27.020 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
operate in concert. This is
certainly consistent
with a catastrophic event.
Whether it is a

06:27.120 --> 06:33.159 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
bomb or some major mechanical
failure remains
to be seen. It also is
consistent with that

06:33.260 --> 06:36.730 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
initial left turn reported on
Greek radar.

06:36.830 --> 06:41.835 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The plane took a 90-degree left
turn initially
when it apparently was in
trouble, and that

06:41.935 --> 06:47.307 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is standard operating procedure
for a flight
crew dealing with a
decompression event and

06:47.407 --> 06:49.142 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
trying to do a rapid descent.

06:49.242 --> 06:54.614 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The idea is not to fly into the
airway beneath
you and potentially hit oncoming
traffic.

06:54.714 --> 06:59.753 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, this is -- in
other words,
you're saying this is consistent
with the

06:59.853 --> 07:03.356 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
little bit, the little that's
known about
what the plane did before it
plunged into

07:03.456 --> 07:05.125 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the water?

07:05.225 --> 07:07.661 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: It is consistent
with a crew
dealing with a rapid
decompression.

07:07.761 --> 07:12.432 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The cause of that rapid
decompression, we
don't know. Was it a bomb or was
it a major

07:12.532 --> 07:14.934 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
mechanical failure are the open
questions.

07:15.035 --> 07:18.772 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Miles, what about
the material
they found floating in the
water? They said

07:18.872 --> 07:25.512 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
two seats, a body part and some
other luggage
and so forth. Do we know
anything based on

07:25.612 --> 07:27.247 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
that?

07:27.347 --> 07:29.316 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: It's a reminder,
of course,
of the human tragedy of all
this.

07:29.416 --> 07:34.654 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it's customary in these
cases that you
see seat cushions and life vests
and baggage

07:34.754 --> 07:41.127 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
because it -- obviously, it
floats. Typically,
it's not very helpful unless, by
some chance,

07:41.227 --> 07:44.597 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the baggage happened to be close
to where
the initial failure occurred.

07:44.698 --> 07:49.302 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What's useful, however, is
knowing where it
is, knowing the ocean currents,
knowing how

07:49.402 --> 07:54.374 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
long it's been in the water. You
can backtrack
to the point of impact. And
that's where you

07:54.474 --> 07:57.677 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
begin your search for the main
body of wreckage
and the black boxes.

07:57.777 --> 08:01.715 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, we heard in
John Yang's
report that that part of the
Mediterranean

08:01.815 --> 08:07.287 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is something like two miles'
deep. What does
that tell us about the
difficulty of this

08:07.387 --> 08:09.089 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
ongoing search?

08:09.189 --> 08:12.959 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MILES O'BRIEN: That it is
difficult. It's
a big challenge, fishing these
boxes out.

08:13.059 --> 08:17.364 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We go through this time and
again. There is
technology off the shelf used by
the military

08:17.464 --> 08:22.602 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
right now which has ejectable,
floatable,
deployable flight data
recorders. There is

08:22.702 --> 08:27.340 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
technology which makes it
possible to stream
this data back in real time, not
unlike the

08:27.440 --> 08:29.943 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
stream that we have just been
talking about.

08:30.043 --> 08:34.080 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the 21st century, the fact
that we have
to listen for pings two miles
beneath the

08:34.180 --> 08:39.085 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
surface of the ocean to find out
a critical
question -- the answer to a
critical question

08:39.185 --> 08:41.654 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is a bit scandalous. We should
do something
about it.

08:41.755 --> 08:46.826 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, Miles, a lot
of people
are saying now that we need to
assume there

08:46.926 --> 08:52.532 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was terrorism involved. Does it
make sense
to do that, in the absence of a
hard answer

08:52.632 --> 08:53.967 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
right now?

08:54.067 --> 08:56.269 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Well, I think we
-- I would
caution our viewers.

08:56.369 --> 09:01.541 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If, in fact, there was some sort
of mechanical
failure here, that's a very
important thing

09:01.641 --> 09:08.214 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to know as soon as possible.
This is a fleet
of aircraft in excess of 6,000
the world over.

09:08.314 --> 09:12.051 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It's an extreme -- it's a
workhorse, and if
there is some fundamental flaw
here which

09:12.152 --> 09:14.721 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
caused this, we need to know
about it yesterday.

09:14.821 --> 09:19.392 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And you're saying
-- but are
we any closer? You're saying
it's just coming

09:19.492 --> 09:21.694 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
very slowly as we get any closer
to answers.

09:21.795 --> 09:26.065 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: You know, absent
a claim of
credit -- and we haven't seen
that just yet

09:26.166 --> 09:32.372 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
-- we're in the dark on this,
and it's -- you
know, eventually, maybe a piece
of fleeting

09:32.472 --> 09:36.776 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
wreckage will offer a clue as to
whether there
was a bomb on board, but I'm
afraid we are

09:36.876 --> 09:40.580 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
going to have to wait for those
black boxes,
the flight data recorder and
cockpit voice

09:40.680 --> 09:42.749 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
recorder, to be discovered at
the bottom of
the sea.

09:42.849 --> 09:45.919 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But, in the
meantime, hold
off on any assumptions?

09:46.019 --> 09:47.320 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: I think so.

09:47.420 --> 09:49.222 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Miles O'Brien, we
thank you.

09:49.322 --> 09:51.458 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: You're welcome,
Judy.

09:51.558 --> 09:55.695 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In the day's
other news: Health
officials reported the number of
pregnant

09:55.795 --> 10:01.434 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
women in the U.S. infected with
the Zika virus
has tripled, to 157.

10:01.534 --> 10:06.139 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Centers for Disease Control
and Prevention
said that it's now including all
women who

10:06.239 --> 10:12.111 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
test positive, regardless of
symptoms. So
far, fewer than a dozen have had
miscarriages

10:12.212 --> 10:14.681 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
or babies born with birth
defects.

10:14.781 --> 10:19.819 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, President Obama got a
briefing
on Zika today, and he urged
Congress to get

10:19.919 --> 10:21.754 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
moving to provide funds.

10:21.855 --> 10:23.923 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the
United States:
Understand that this is not
something where

10:24.023 --> 10:30.330 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we can build a wall to prevent.
Mosquitoes
don't go through customs. To the
extent that

10:30.430 --> 10:34.701 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we're not handling this thing on
the front
end, we're going to have bigger
problems on

10:34.801 --> 10:36.569 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the back end.

10:36.669 --> 10:43.009 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, for those of you who are
listening, tell
your members of Congress, get on
the job on

10:43.109 --> 10:44.744 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
this.

10:44.844 --> 10:49.148 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The U.S. Senate
has passed
a $1.1 billion bill to fight the
virus. A

10:49.249 --> 10:53.686 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
House-passed bill totals just
